HEADWORD: Azalea
<hw>A*za"le*a</hw> <pr>(?; 97)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Azaleas</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ dry, --
so called because supposed to grow best in dry ground.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of showy flowering shrubs, mostly natives
of China or of North America; false honeysuckle. The genus is scarcely
distinct from <gen>Rhododendron</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

